Developing skills on one's main instrument through the practice of technical exercises and the study of the mandatory repertoire. Transcribing and sight-reading.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at developing a good sound quality, and finding one's idiosyncratic playing style on the main instrument.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion the course the students: * are able to perform the first year mandatory repertoire; * know the basic modes (2nd year requirements), * analyze different interpretations (based on transcribed material) * prepare a 2x20-minute concert program; * will have acquired knowledge in combining different styles, based on personal experience.
